<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-31T03:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-31T03:54:00-05:00" n="969" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90F27/12–3145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-31T12:00:00+03:06">December
                                    31, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>446. Deptel 380, December 29. Foreign Minister is still in Mecca with
                            King and will return to Jidda late today. I shall immediately <pb facs="1009" n="997" xml:id="pg_997"/> press for inclusion of 6
                            months’ notice in SAG (Saudi Arabian Govt) written reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>